comments.body:
@coandco, would a template-based approach as described in https://github.com/containers/podman/commit/8684d41e387a work for you?

Starting with Podman v4.2, you can throw a Kubernetes YAML file at a systemd template which will run the workload in systemd.  I will write detailed docs and a blog on that soon.

[Quadlet](https://github.com/containers/quadlet) may also be worth having a look at.
